Command from kubectl ==> Authentication ==> Authorization ==> Admission Controllers ==> Create Pod

kubectl exec pod/kube-apiserver-node -n kube-system -- kube-apiserver -h | grep -i "enable-admission-plugins"

Types of AdmissionControllers-
1. Mutating(It changes the config before operation) 2. Validating(It vlidates conditions are met before operation)

In lab we create a Validating Admissioncontroller (checking securitycontext if run as root is specified or not)
